# Environment Configuration for Local Development
# Copy this to .env for local development (never commit .env to git!)

# === DEVELOPMENT TOKENS (Local Only) ===
# These are for local development only. 
# Production uses Wrangler secrets - see setup commands below.

# API Token for regular user operations
SIGNALQ_API_TOKEN=$SIGNALQ_API_TOKEN

# Admin Token for administrative operations
SIGNALQ_ADMIN_TOKEN=$SIGNALQ_ADMIN_TOKEN

# === CUSTOM DOMAIN CONFIGURATION ===
# Set custom domain for production deployment
# Leave empty to use workers.dev fallback
# CUSTOM_DOMAIN=signal-q.example.com

# === BUILD INFORMATION ===
# Automatically set in CI/CD pipeline
GIT_SHA=local-development
BUILD_TIME=2025-01-01T00:00:00.000Z
NODE_ENV=development

# === CLOUDFLARE CONFIGURATION ===
# Account ID for Cloudflare Workers (optional for local dev)
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=your-account-id-here

# API Token for Cloudflare Workers (optional for local dev)
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=your-api-token-here

# === PRODUCTION SECRETS SETUP ===
# Do NOT put production secrets in this file!
# Use Wrangler secrets for production:
#
# wrangler secret put SIGNALQ_API_TOKEN
# wrangler secret put SIGNALQ_ADMIN_TOKEN
#
# For GitHub Actions deployment:
# 1. Add secrets to repository settings:
#    - CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN (required for deployment)
#    - CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID (required for deployment)
#    - SIGNALQ_API_TOKEN_PROD (for production testing)
#    - SIGNALQ_ADMIN_TOKEN_PROD (for admin operations)
#    - SIGNALQ_API_TOKEN_STAGING (for staging testing)
#
# === REQUIRED SECRETS LIST ===
# The following secrets must be configured for full functionality:
# 
# Repository Secrets (GitHub):
# - CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN: Cloudflare API token for deployment
# - CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID: Cloudflare account ID
# - SIGNALQ_API_TOKEN_PROD: Production user API token
# - SIGNALQ_ADMIN_TOKEN_PROD: Production admin API token  
# - SIGNALQ_API_TOKEN_STAGING: Staging user API token (optional)
#
# Wrangler Secrets (Per Environment):
# - SIGNALQ_API_TOKEN: User token for regular operations
# - SIGNALQ_ADMIN_TOKEN: Admin token for deployment actions

# === LOCAL DEVELOPMENT NOTES ===
# - Copy this file to .env for local development
# - Never commit .env to version control
# - The worker falls back to hardcoded dev tokens if env vars not set
# - Use 'npm run dev' for cloud development mode
# - Use 'npm run dev:fallback' for firewall-safe local mode